Codecademy HTML & CSS ANSWERS HTML Basics II / Ordered lists /3

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title>Lists</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>List of my favorite things</h1>
		<ol>
			<li>Raindrops on roses</li>
			<li>Whiskers on kittens</li>
			<li>Bright copper kettles</li>
			<li>Warm woolen mittens</li>
		</ol>
		<h2> List of things I find just OK</h2>
		<ol>
		<li> Codecademy </li>
		<li> Google </li>
		<li> My Country name is BANGLADESH </li>
		</ol>
		
	</body>
</html>

Codecademy HTML & CSS ANSWERS HTML Basics II / Unordered lists/5

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title>Unordered Lists</title>
	</head>
	<body>	
	<h1><p> 'Some random thoughts'</p></h1>
	<p> Random List </p>
	<ul>
	  <li>random thing 1 </li>
	  <li>random thing 2 </li>
	  <li>random thing 3 </li>
	  <li>random thing 4 </li>
	  
	</ul>	
	</body>
</html>

Codecademy HTML & CSS ANSWERS HTML Basics II /Lists inside a list /6

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<title>Nested lists</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<ol>
			<li>Dad's interests
				<ul>
					<li>football</li>
					<li>knitting</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
			<li>Mom's interests
				<ul>
					<li>hating football</li>
					<li>skydiving</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
		</ol>
		<ul>Favorite Boys</ul> <ul>Favorite Girls</ul>
		<ol>
		<li> Favorite Boys
		<ul>
		<li>Name 1</li>
		<li>Name 2</li>
		<li>Name3 </li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		<li> Favorite Girls
		<ul>
		<li>Name 1</li>
		<li>Name 2</li>
		<li>Name 3</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
		</ol>
	</body>
	
